<subSubSection id="F8F90BC7FFF5FFC76BC75BDDFDCEFD14" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B05C584CFFF5FFC76BC75BDDFDCEFD14" blockId="14.[192,1440,461,648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="8297845EFFF5FFC76BC75BDDFEBEFE76" bold="true" box="[192,323,461,485]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species of the bifurca species group are marked by a contrasting pattern of black and white setae, making them some of the most easily recognizable within the genus. Additionally, they are among the few species of 
<emphasis id="8297845EFFF5FFC76A9B581DFD8FFDB6" box="[412,626,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Traumatomutilla</emphasis>
that show almost no variation in color or setae patterns. Although the two included species are separated by multiple structural features, as noted in their diagnoses below, they are most readily and easily differentiated by color pattern, particularly in the mesosomal stripes and 
<collectionCode id="D6F2C089FFF5FFC76BF15860FEF5FD1B" box="[246,264,624,648]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">T</collectionCode>
2 markings (
<figureCitation id="28D844C9FFF5FFC76AA5587FFE04FD14" box="[418,505,623,647]" captionStart="Figures 26–27" captionStartId="18.[192,287,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[242,1391,220,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[242,1391,220,1844]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 26–27. Traumatomutilla bifurca (Klug, 1821), ♀, lectotype, line 2mm. 26) Dorsal habitus. 27) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674809/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="28D844C9FFF5FFC76902587FFDDBFD14" box="[517,550,623,647]" captionStart="Figures 46–50" captionStartId="23.[192,287,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[242,1391,216,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[242,1391,216,1840]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 46–50. Traumatomutilla oxira Casal, 1969, ♀, holotype. 46) Dorsal habitus, line 2mm. 47) Lateral habitus, line 2mm. 48) Head, frontal view. 49) T6 (pygidium), posterior view. 50) Holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674821/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">46</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
